            <thetext>You are automaticaly binding command properties to target properties. One of that bindable properties is value.

Now the problems: 
1. All bindings are unidirectional, from command to target; Should be bidirectional

2. Targets witch have execute() function and a value property like checkbox or radiobox are firing twice if the value of command is changing on execute. Cause of binding and common execute behavior of commands.</thetext>
